###
### GET All Users
## Expected result: Returns array of all users (passwords excluded)

GET {{userendpoint}} HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
x-api-key: blahblah

###
### GET User by ID
## Expected result: Returns single user object without password fields

GET {{userendpoint}}/{{testUserId}} HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
x-api-key: blahblah

###
### POST: Create New User
## Expected result: Creates user with hashed password, returns 201 with user ID

POST {{userendpoint}} HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
x-api-key: blahblah

{
    "username": "validationtest",
    "cognitoId": "821544b4-70c1-7045-3146-1785328f53f4",
    "phonenumber": "0871233456",
    "email": "11381deddd15@bing.ie"
}

###
### POST: Create User with Duplicate Email
## Expected result: Should fail with 400 "existing email" error

POST {{userendpoint}} HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
x-api-key: blahblah

{
    "username": "duplicate",
    "cognitoId": "us-east-1:duplicate-cognito-id",
    "phonenumber": "0871234567",
    "email": "s100253815@bing.ie"
}

###
### POST: Create User with Invalid Phone Number
## Expected result: Should fail validation (if middleware active)

POST {{userendpoint}} HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
x-api-key: blahblah

{
    "username": "badphone",
    "cognitoId": "us-east-1:badphone-cognito-id",
    "password": "Password123",
    "phonenumber": "123456",
    "email": "badphone@test.ie"
}

###
### PUT: Update User by ID
## Expected result: Updates user fields, returns 200

PUT {{userendpoint}}/{{testUserId}} HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: blahblah

{
    "username": "updatedname",
    "phonenumber": "0871274675",
    "email": "updated@test.ie"
}

###
### DELETE: Delete User by ID
## Expected result: Removes user, returns 200 with deletion message

DELETE {{userendpoint}}/691462eb0a73737c0ae4b2d9 HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
x-api-key: blahblah

###
### ============================================
### COGNITO-BASED AUTHENTICATED ROUTES
### ============================================

###
### POST: Sync Cognito User to MongoDB
## Expected result: Creates or updates user based on Cognito JWT, syncs lastLogin
## Requires: Valid Cognito access token in Authorization header
## has to be from the CognitoIdentityServiceProvider.7da2gmun3puk0lh5ord5b6f5vj.821544b4-70c1-7045-3146-1785328f53f4.idToken in the response of the login route in the auth.http file

POST {{userendpoint}}/cognito/sync HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{cognitoToken}}

{
    "cognitoId": "prj300@proton.me",
    "email": "prj300@proton.me"  
}

###
### GET: Get Current User Profile (Cognito)
## Expected result: Returns authenticated user's profile (no password fields)
## Requires: Valid Cognito access token

GET {{userendpoint}}/cognito/me HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{cognitoToken}}

###
### PUT: Update Current User Profile (Cognito)
## Expected result: Updates username/phonenumber with validation, returns updated profile
## Requires: Valid Cognito access token

PUT {{userendpoint}}/cognito/me HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{cognitoToken}}

{
    "username": "newusername",
    "phonenumber": "0871234567"
}

###
### PUT: Update Current User Profile - Invalid Username
## Expected result: Should fail with 400 "Invalid username format"

PUT {{userendpoint}}/cognito/me HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{cognitoToken}}

{
    "username": "invalid@user!"
}

###
### PUT: Update Current User Profile - Invalid Phone
## Expected result: Should fail with 400 "Invalid phone number format"

PUT {{userendpoint}}/cognito/me HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{cognitoToken}}

{
    "phonenumber": "123"
}

